Apple has launched its HomePod speaker, which will start shipping from 9 February. The smart speaker will be available for preorder from 26 January, priced at $349. Apple stated that the speaker will be available in the US, UK, and Australia as part of the launch wave. The HomePod will then be made available in France and Germany “this spring”. The HomePod is compatible with the iPhone 5s or later, iPad Pro, iPad Air or later, iPad mini 2 or later, or iPod touch (6th gen) with iOS 11.2.5 or later.